  "text": "Research by [CITATION_1] found that ovariectomy in animal experiments increase expression of TH. TH relatively little in animal experiments but can raise significantly when the levels decline after ovariectomy. Sympathetic axons releasing norepinephrine cause smooth muscle contraction, vasoconstriction and increase vaginal muscle tone. Finally increase of sympathetic nerve fibers in low estrogen state causes a decrease in blood flow and a decrease in lubrication. This is consistent with the vasoconstriction, decreased blood flow, decreased lubrication in menopause and after ovariectomy surgery in humans and experimental animals. Estrogen causes a decrease in the expression of TH and reduced complaints occur.",
